{"ts":"2026-07-06T12:33:07.412Z","seq":38,"event":"agent.invoke","agent":"04-backend-developer","prompt":"Build the backend using #file:artifacts\\architecture\\handoff-contract.md as your architecture contract and #file:{ba_handoff} for business requirements. For deeper context, the architecture package (tech stack, TDD, LLD, API spec, data dictionary, security, deployment, ADRs, DB strategy) is under #file:artifacts/architecture/ and the full requirements package is under #file:artifacts/requirements/ -- read specific files as needed.\n\nIMPORTANT: This stage must produce real, working, runnable code -- not just documentation or pseudocode. Skip if there already else create unless specified to do differentlyWrite actual source files (routes/controllers, services, models, request/response validation) implementing every endpoint described in the architecture contract.Do not stop at a design description -- the code must actually run. Create only mising artifacts.\n\nCorrelation ID: WF-1783340956452. Create only mising artifacts.","currentStage":"backend"}
