{"ts":"2026-07-06T12:33:08.216Z","seq":41,"event":"agent.invoke","agent":"06-database-admin","prompt":"Design the database using #file:artifacts\\architecture\\database-strategy.md as your primary conceptual input. For deeper context, the rest of the architecture package is under #file:artifacts/architecture/ and the requirements package is under #file:artifacts/requirements/ -- read specific files as needed. Backend output (#file:artifacts\\backend\\handoff-contract.md) is optional context -- do not block on it; if backend-dependent decisions cannot be confirmed, record a coordination note in openlog.md. If the Requirements or Architecture package is missing entirely, stop immediately, return an explicit missing-input error, and mark BLOCKED.\n\nIMPORTANT: This stage must produce real, runnable artifacts -- not just a design document. Skip if there already else create unless specified to do differently Write actual migration scripts / schema DDL files that can be executed to create the real schema, consistent with the models used in the backend code. If seed data is expected, include a real seed script too.\n\nCorrelation ID: WF-1783340956452. Create only missing artifacts.","currentStage":"database"}
