{"ts":"2026-07-06T12:34:55.477Z","seq":45,"event":"agent.invoke","agent":"05-qa-engineer","prompt":"Run full QA using #file:artifacts\\frontend\\handoff-contract.md, #file:artifacts\\backend\\handoff-contract.md, and #file:artifacts\\database\\handoff-contract.md as your primary contracts, plus #file:artifacts\\frontend\\ui-specification.md and #file:artifacts\\backend\\backend-design.md for behavior detail. For deeper context, the full requirements package is under #file:artifacts/requirements/ and the full architecture package is under #file:artifacts/architecture/ -- read specific files as needed. Also read the full implementation directly under apps/frontend/, apps/backend/, apps/database/, and artifacts/database/ for real test-writing context.\n\nIMPORTANT: You must ACTUALLY EXECUTE tests end-to-end against the real code -- do not review the code and describe hypothetical results. Concretely:\n1. Start the backend (and frontend, if applicable) locally.\n2. Run the backend's own unit test suite and capture the real pass/fail output.\n3. Execute real end-to-end scenarios: make actual HTTP requests against the running backend covering the main user flows (e.g. register, login, create/read/update/delete the core resources), and check the actual responses.\n4. If a frontend exists, verify it actually loads and can complete at least one full user flow against the real backend.\n5. Save the RAW command output/logs from all of the above into test-execution-log.md as evidence.\n6. Only after that, produce your full QA artifact package (coverage-matrix.md, gap-analysis.md, qa-blockers.md, quality-report.md, handoff-contract.md), referencing the evidence in test-execution-log.md. Every defect you report must be reproducible from the evidence log, not inferred from reading code.\n\nCorrelation ID: WF-1783340956452.","currentStage":"qa"}
